News & Press > News




CHAIR 2 WON THE NYCXDESIGN AWARD IN NEW YORK 



 Cappellini is once again under the spotlight of the cultural debate on interior design winning a much-coveted prize at NYCxDesign Awards with the Chair 2 designed by the Tel Aviv-based Bakery Studio. The award is organized by the prestigious magazine Interior Design during ICFF in order to highlight the best designs amongst over 500 brands who took part at the Fair. 

7 July 2017 

News & Press > News




25 HOURS HOTEL IN ZURICH 



 The custom-made version of the Juli09 chair by Werner Aissingler furnishes the 25hours Hotel Zurich, an independent universe where the worlds and cultures of art and finance converge in the center of Zurich.

7 July 2017 

News & Press > News




NEW CAPPELLINI-HAWORTH DUAL BRAND SHOWROOM IN ZURICH 



 Cappellini together with Haworth celebrated at the end of June  the opening of the new showroom concept in Zurich that explores solutions for the future of work. Over 125 designers, architects, customers and industry partners joined on the evening to discover the new space which blends products from both brands together in a variety of applications that reflect the changing nature of work. 
 

7 July 2017 

News & Press > News




NEW CAPPELLINI-HAWORTH DUAL BRAND SHOWROOM IN AMSTERDAM 



 Cappellini together with Haworth inaugurated at the beginning of June a new dual –brand showroom in  Amsterdam. The showroom sits in the beautiful harbour area of Houthaven. It shows Haworth's latest workplace solutions next to iconic Cappellini pieces.

7 July 2017 

News & Press > News




CAPPELLINI @ NEOCON CHICAGO 



 Cappellini participated at the Neocon Fair in Chicago within Haworth’s booth with the main products from the Collection which are suitable for contract spaces among which the Elan sofa, the Hi pad chair, the Tate Stool, the armchair Low Pad and Lotus by Jasper Morrison, the Basket sofa by the Bouroullec brothers, the Telo Lounge armchair by Sebastian Herkner and the Bong and Gong small tables  by Giulio Cappellini.

7 July 2017 

News & Press > News




CAPPELLINI @ ICFF NEW YORK 



 In occasion of the recent ICFF Fair in New York, Cappellini presented the 2017 Collection at the Cappellini SoHo showroom, recently renovated, to reflect a new artistic design concept created by Giulio Cappellini. The design blends accuracy and passion in a rotation of neutral shades and a blaze of colours and decorations. The new store concept represents in a contemporary and universal way the Company’s Identity always oriented to the future, with strong connections with Art and Fashion. 

7 July 2017 

News & Press > News




New York Cappellini showroom renovation 



 Our New York flagshipstore  in SoHo has been recently renovated with the new store concept which represents in a contemporary and universal way the Company’s Identity always oriented to the future, with strong connections with Art and Fashion. This combination results in a sober and rigorous space to showcase the variety of shapes, colors and materials of the Cappellini products.

8 May 2017 

News & Press > News




Cappellini at Millesime, Philadelphia 



 Recently Cappellini and Millesime, located in the Old City neighborhood of Philadelphia, outlined a partnership with a new branded display.

2 May 2017 

News & Press > News




Hobo Hotel in Stockholm 



 The new Cappellini Hobo sofa at the center of the new Hobo Hotel in Stockholm realized by the German Werner Aissingler Studio. A new concept of hotel-community where travelers can feel at ease in an informal and vintage atmosphere. Picture by  Patricia Parinejad.

28 April 2017 

News & Press > News




Award to Giulio Cappellini 



On April 6th at La Triennale in Milan, Giulio Cappellini was honored with the award “Milano Design Award Lifetime Achievement” to have marked the history of the Fuorisalone.

28 April 2017 

News & Press > News




Exhibition “ An emotional journey into colours” by ILVA VERNICI 



 The world of lacquering of ILVA Vernici was explored with an artistic installation and with a few cabinets of the Cappellini collection declined in several red shades in the city center in Foro Bonaparte during the Design Week.

28 April 2017 

News & Press > News




Cappellini collaborates with Eurojersey at the Milan Design Week 



 The encounter between two exceptional Italian realities, CAPPELLINI and EUROJERSEY, gave birth to a joint project inspired by the most modern trends sharing common values and contents marking the two brands which is embodied by the new sofa MILL HOME. EUROJERSEY is making MILL HOME even more special dressing it with its exceptional fabrics featuring the warp kint patented technology of SENSITIVE® FABRICS by EUROJERSEY, an ideal combination of adaptability and performance to match the equation “Quality +...
28 April 2017 

News & Press > News




Cappellini at White in the City 



 White in the City is a project that involved some of the most prestigious locations during the Milan Design Week. An itinerary that represented the white in its thousand chromatic and symbolic faces under the Artistic Direction of Giulio Cappellini. In the courtyard of honor of the Pinacoteca di Brera, besides the architectural installation of Giulio Cappellini, a few iconic products of the collection such as the Bong tables and the Thinking Man’s Chair by Jasper Morrison have been displayed.  At Palazzo...
28 April 2017 

News & Press > News




“The Cappellini Temporary Tower” by Leonardo Talarico 



 During the Milan Design Week, Cappellini presented “The Cappellini Temporary Tower”, a spectacular artwork designed by Leonardo Talarico for the urban context of Largo Treves in Milan, a crossing point between the main streets of the Design Week. A massive mechanical arm rises to suspend in the air Tate iconic chairs designed by Jasper Morrison for Cappellini, here seen in green. The Cappellini Temporary Tower recasts the tree in a post-industrial light paying homage to nature and its awakening, coming every...
28 April 2017 

News & Press > News




The “Cappellini Home” at the Milanese showroom in via Santa Cecilia 



 Within the Milanese showroom during the Design Week, Cappellini expressed a way of  living according to its own principles of freedom by blending graphic pieces with products characterized with their warm and modern palette of colours. Green and orange shades matching with nonchalance natural colours such as beige and sand. Besides a few Tube Chairs by Joe Colombo were displayed in a dedicated installation within the showroom.

28 April 2017 
 









 








